comments.body:
@RKSimon Is the following `V1Needed` correct to determine whether the second shuffle argument is needed or it's OK for it be undef/poison? Essentially:

```c++
unsigned OldMaskSize = OldMask.size();
bool V1Needed =
      std::any_of(OldMask.begin(), OldMask.end(),
                  [OldMaskSize](int Idx) { return Idx > OldMaskSize; });
if (V1Needed)
    return foldBinaryShuffleOfCastops(V0, V1, OldMask, I);
else
    return foldUnaryShuffleOfCastops(V0, OldMask, I);
```

I'm not sure if it's alright to check the bound on indices like this, and if so what should the bound be: the mask size or something like `CastDstTy->getNumElements()`. Working on fleshing out `foldUnaryShuffleOfCastops`.
